title: For Sale/Trade:  BCM 14.5" Middy AR-15 for Sale or Vehicle Trade
postcontent:
I am selling/trading my BCM 14.5" Mid-Length AR-15.

It has a 14.5" Barrel with mid-length gas system and both the upper and lower receivers are BCM (top of the line AR manufacture). It is dressed in Magpul gear with the MIAD pistol grip, CTR collapsible stock, extended trigger guard and XTM rail panels. It also has a Tangodown vertical grip with cutout for the pressure switch for the weaponlight. The weaponlight is a Surefire M591, which is the same one used by the military in Iraq and Afghanistan currently. 

The rail system is a Midwest Industries free floating monolithic aluminum rail that directly mounts to the barrel receiver and not the delta ring.

The optic is an Aimpoint PRO (Patrol Rifle Optic) red dot that co-witnesses with the Troy Battlesight rear flip up sight and the A2 front sight. Both the rear flip up sight and the front A2 sight have tritium inserts that glow int he dark without needing any light.

I have a Spikes Tactical ST-T2 buffer and Tubbs flat wire buffer spring in it and KNS anti-rotation hammer and trigger pins installed. I also have installed a BCM Gunfighter charging handle installed on it for easier one handed operation.

I'll toss in six 30 round magazines, 2 metal BCM mags and 4 Magpul PMags.

This AR is fully Mil-Spec, none of that crappy Commercial stuff they have out now.

I have about 300 rounds through it so it is broken in and ready for battle or range use and is VERY dependable. I has never had a jam, failure to feed or failure to extract. It is cleaned thoroughly each time its shot and put away lubed and ready to go at a moments notice.

I have $2800 in the rifle and I am asking $2700 for it or possible even trade for vehicle or equal or higher value.

This is a top of the line AR-15 and the value will only go up, specially if there is another attempted ban or double that price if there is an actual ban on these.

Email with make/model, miles, running condition, any issues it has and I will email you back if interested so you can send me pictures. Must be dependable vehicle.
